Class ValueSupply<A>

  • java.lang.Object
    • dev.marksman.kraftwerk.ValueSupply<A>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - the element type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functor.Functor<A,dev.marksman.enhancediterables.EnhancedIterable<?>>, dev.marksman.enhancediterables.EnhancedIterable<A>, dev.marksman.enhancediterables.ImmutableIterable<A>, dev.marksman.enhancediterables.ImmutableNonEmptyIterable<A>, dev.marksman.enhancediterables.NonEmptyIterable<A>, java.lang.Iterable<A>

    public final class ValueSupply<A>
extends java.lang.Object
implements dev.marksman.enhancediterables.ImmutableNonEmptyIterable<A>
    An infinite sequence of values of type A.

    A ValueSupply does not have internal state, so it can be iterated multiple times, and for each time will return the same sequence.

    Each element of a ValueSupply is lazily computed, therefore, a ValueSupply only requires a small, constant amount of memory.
